    "description": "Ferguson's API Product for exchanging Product related data with 3rd party companies. \n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\nTo discover what products have been exposed to you, you can use pagination at the products plural URI endpoint and find out the total number and an array of products and their details. You can continue to make subsequent API calls that return back new product details by passing back the offset string as a parameter.\n\n&nbsp;\n## Sample API calls to discover what products you've got access too:\n\n### Fetch inital product data that you've been given access to with a limit paramater or accept the default limit of 10:\n```JSON\n[GET]/v1/products?limit=100\n[GET]/v1/products\n```\n### In the inital response you see an offset attribute returned to you.\n```JSON\n{\n  \"limit\" : 100,\n  \"offset\" : \"MjYzNAWzOjMuM8212OTE\",\n  \"results\" : [ {...} ],\n  \"total\": 1891\n}\n```\n### For proper pagination in subsequent calls you will need to pass in the offset string as a query parameter.\n```JSON\n[GET]/v1/products?limit=100&offset=NDkyO234wNzozLjIyMTI220NKJ\n```\n<details>\n  <summary>Click to see full returned response</summary>\n```JSON\n{\n\"limit\": 1,\n\"offset\": \"NDkyO234wNzozLjIyMTI220NKJ\",\n\"total\": 3754,\n\"results\": [\n    {\n        \"FLD Attributes\": {\n            \"New Features 01\": \"One-piece bracket, for suspended or hard-lid ceilings\",\n            \"New Features 02\": \"Allows installation before ceiling tile, eliminate messy cutting tools\",\n            \"New Features 03\": \"Sizes 24\\\" / 610 mm and 48\\\" / 1219 mm\",\n            \"Web Display Name\": \"24 in. Adjustable Bracket Assembly\"\n        },\n        \"Product Attributes\": {\n            \"Altcode\": \"VA240AB1ADJ-NR\",\n            \"Description\": \"24 IN AB1 ADJ BRKT ASSY\",\n            \"Digital Assets\": \"https://api.ferguson.com/dar-step-service/dar/productassets/4928707\"\n            \"Long Description\": \"24 Inch AB1 Adjustable Bracket Assembly\",\n            \"Master Product Id\": \"4928707\",\n            \"Primary Vendor Id\": \"1485\",\n            \"Product Category\": \"Pipe Fittings;Copper Elbows;\",\n            \"UPC Code\": \"883481378369\",\n            \"Vendor Product Code\": \"A240AB1ADJ\"\n        },\n        \"eCatalog Attributes\": {\n            \"ANSI UOM\": \"EA\",\n            \"Qty Multiple\": \"1\",\n            \"UNSPSC\": \"40141719\"\n        },\n        \"eCommerce Attributes\": {\n            \"Fitting Size 1\": \"24 in\",\n            \"Fitting Sizes\": \"24 in\",\n            \"Specifications - FM Approved\": \"No\",\n            \"Specifications - UL Listed\": \"No\"\n        },\n        \"id\": \"4928707\",\n        \"name\": \"VA240AB1ADJ-NR 24 IN AB1 ADJ BRKT ASSY\",\n        \"status\": \"enabled\",\n        \"type\": \"product\"\n      }\n   ]\n}\n  \n```\n</details>\n\nAt the end of the list, the offset 'RkZGRkZGRkZGRkZGRkZGRg==' (translates to 'FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF') is returned. If this offset is then passed to the proxy, you will recieve an error denoting you are at the end of the product list.\n```JSON\n{\n   \"message\": [\n    \"You have reached the end of the product list.\"\n],\n\"error code\": \"400\",\n\"reason\": \"Bad Request\",\n\"contact\": \"https://developer.ferguson.com\"\n}\n```\nTo restart from the beginning of the products, just remove the offset query parameter.\n&nbsp;\n\n## Sample API call to return a specific Product Id:\nOnce you know what product ids you've got access too, you can also pull up that specific Product's details and see all of its attributes. Keep in mind, the attributes returned are the exact same ones that were returned during the bulk API call mentioned above.\n&nbsp;\n### Fetch product 31523:\n```JSON\n[GET]/v1/products/31523\n```\n<details>\n  <summary>Click to see full returned response</summary>\n```JSON\n{\n\"results\": [\n    {\n        \"FLD Attributes\": {\n            \"New Features 01\": \"Wrot copper\",\n            